    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Just took a look @Morhaus thx for pointing that out.\n\nI think the solution implemented in #1170 brings more problems than it actually solves. \nIt makes reasoning about widget states difficult.\n\nRegarding the `currentRefined` widget, if it depends on other facets, then it should reference those facets and react on their changes.\n\nIt could even just use the attribute name for the display and let users provide an array of `attribute => label` for the display, and extract the refined values from the helper's state. IMHO that is the way to go about it.\n\nNot sure if I'm missing something here @Morhaus \n",
