    "body": "> Regarding the currentRefinedWidget, you cannot infer what actions resulted in given helper state just from looking at its serialized representation.\n\nCould you give an example?\n\nWhat is it you call `virtual widgets`? widgets that have no UI? \n\nRegarding default widget state, IMHO widgets should take their state from the helper. When no state matched, then it can suggest its own default state but set it on the helper, not just internally.\n",
